# Current Datetime

Whenever you need the current datetime in UTC, use the following command:

```bash
date -u +%Y%m%d%H%M%S
```

This will return the current datetime in UTC in the format YYYYMMDDHHMMSS.

## Usage Guidelines

This is especially important when generating filename for supabase migrations.
